From: PS3 Custom Toolchain
Subject: [PATCH] config.sub: recognize ps3-kernel ELF target

Recognize the parallel kernel-side PPU target as a freestanding ELF
configuration during config.sub canonicalization.  The GCC backend
configuration already maps the canonical target through the target
tables; this change only lets configure reach those tables.

--- a/config.sub
+++ b/config.sub
@@ -1769,6 +1769,16 @@ case $kernel-$os in
 	linux-gnu* | linux-dietlibc* | linux-android* | linux-newlib* \
 		   | linux-musl* | linux-relibc* | linux-uclibc* )
 		;;
+	kernel-elf*)
+		case $cpu-$vendor in
+			powerpc64-ps3)
+				;;
+			*)
+				echo "Invalid configuration \`$1': Kernel \`$kernel' not known to work with OS \`$os'." 1>&2
+				exit 1
+				;;
+		esac
+		;;
 	uclinux-uclibc* )
 		;;
 	-dietlibc* | -newlib* | -musl* | -relibc* | -uclibc* )
